  "prompt": "How do I verify my Twitter account?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the process to verify your Twitter account typically involves the following steps. However, please keep in mind that Twitter's policies and procedures can change, so it\u2019s a good idea to check their official help center or support pages for the most current information.\n\n1. **Eligibility**: Ensure that your account is eligible for verification. Generally, Twitter considers accounts of public interest, representing notable individuals or brands.\n\n2. **Profile Requirements**: Make sure your profile is complete:\n   - A verified phone number and a confirmed email address\n   - A bio\n   - A profile picture\n   - A birthday (for personal accounts, not applicable to companies or brands)\n   - A website (if applicable)\n   - Public tweets (accounts must be set to public)\n\n3. **Active Use & Adherence**: Your account should be active and in good standing with Twitter's rules.\n\n4. **Submit a Request**: Go to Twitter\u2019s verification request form in the app settings (if they have made it available to you) and provide your account information and reason for verification. You might have to provide URLs or other references to establish notability.\n\n5. **Provide Identification**: You may need to provide a government-issued ID or other appropriate documentation to verify your identity.\n\n6. **Wait for Response**: After submitting your application, wait for Twitter to respond. This process can take several weeks.\n\nRemember, Twitter does not guarantee verification for all applicants and can revoke verification at their discretion. Also, Twitter has historically paused and resumed verification processes, so availability can vary.",
